BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260309T073000
DTEND:20260309T190600
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-1.792ft at 07:30\n-2.769ft at 19:06\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Mix of mid-period NW swell edges up while short-period NW swell eases\, fo
 r mainly thigh-waist high+ waves at good exposures. \n\nWinds looking ligh
 t offshore most of the morning\, shift light+ SW for the afternoon. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260310T073000
DTEND:20260310T190600
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.532ft at 07:30\n-2.969ft at 19:06\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Blend of shorter-period NW swell lingers as traces of fresh long-period S 
 Southern Hemi creep in\, for mainly knee to waist high+ zone surf. \n\nLig
 ht/variable winds expected in the morning\, turn light SW in the afternoon
 \, maintaining nice conditions. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260311T080000
DTEND:20260311T190000
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.934ft at 08:00\n-2.981ft at 19:00\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Fresh mix of longer-period steep-angled S Southern Hemi and NW swell gradu
 ally fills in\, setting up waist to shoulder high waves at good exposures\
 , while long-period focal points hit head high+ during the afternoon. \n\n
 Light/variable winds due all day for mostly clean conditions. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260312T090000
DTEND:20260312T191200
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.964ft at 09:00\n-2.942ft at 19:12\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Selective\, steep-angled\, long-period S Southern Hemi swell tops out\, as
  modest scale NW swell lingers. Good southerly exposures are chest to head
  high\, while standouts go 1-2' overhead on sets. \n\nWinds looking light\
 , primarily offshore all day\, keeping town conditions clean. 
END:VEVENT
